Data sources

Chemistry data shown on the maps is from Siegel et al.(Geology 2004). The total dissolved solids data is from Prof.Kurt Hollochers measurements as reported in his 2002 and 2011 field guides.

The fault data is from the National Atlas of the United States. (2005). Fault Lines: Geology of the Conterminous United States, 2005. National Atlas of the United States. Available at: http://purl.stanford.edu/tt369vk9000
